Eloquentia is personified in the same way in 12. 7: also by Cicero, Brut. § 330: cp. dictio, de Or. i. ᾖ 1 57 (educenda deinde dictio est . . . in aciem forensem).—On the other hand, the subject might well enough be ‘ orator,' to be supplied out of the context, as often: we should then have to read ipse in 3 5 and nobilitatus in 36.
